and investigative skills.Proven organizational and time-management skills.Ability to recognize, respect, and work with individuals and groups with diverse backgrounds and perspectives.Expert computer skills, familiarity with Windows operating systems, and experience using general-purpose application software for documents, presentations, spreadsheets, and virtual meetings.Exceptional ability to learn and adapt to new technologies.May be required to fill and lift boxes that could weigh up to 50 pounds/22.68 kilograms.May be working with items that are older in nature, damaged, soiled, damp or contain mold. Appropriate PPE will be provided when handling these materialsFor additional information and to apply on-line, please visit: https://urcareers.uregina.ca/postings/17688 Compensation $53,617.20 - $72,381.40 Closes: 5 December, 2024 University of Regina Library Regina , SK Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
