 improve student literacy, and be familiar with and knowledgeable about current Literacy practices, including reading intervention strategies, assessment and evaluation techniques, best practices, and curriculum surrounding literacy; commit to the District’s and school’s goals to improve the success of First Nations students; communicate with parents and guardians; be willing and flexible to teach other subjects; be willing and able to travel throughout the District, when required; be physically capable to perform the duties of this position. Essential Qualifications: BC Certified and qualified with a Master’s Degree/Diploma in Teacher-Librarianship;Valid Class 5 BC driver’s license. Successful experience in supporting individual student learning in a multi-grade classroom. Inquiries can be directed to the Principal of Gold River Secondary School – sbroderick@viw.sd84.bc.ca 250-283-2538, Ray Watkins Elementary School- ntoth@viw.sd84.bc.ca or at 250‑283‑2220. Interested applicants are required to submit their application by September 12, 2024 at 10:00 AM as follows:Current SD84 Certified Teachers may apply via this link: Temporary Teacher LibrarianThe District will only be accepting applications via the above links. Emailed and/or paper copy applications will not be accepted. If you require any assistance with your application, please contact hr@viw.sd84.bc.ca Compensation $61,488-$109,520 Closes: 12 December, 2024 Vancouver Island West (School District 84) Gold River , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
